The recipe :

*** Setup athena release 15.1.0

* If you want to use only the PAUconversionFlagTool, you only need to check out PhotonAnalysisUtils and use the jobO PAUanalysis_jobOptions_15.1.0.py

* If you want to use the PhotonRecoveryTool, you have to follow the following steps...

cmt co -r CaloClusterCorrection-00-06-04 Calorimeter/CaloClusterCorrection
cd Calorimeter/CaloClusterCorrection/cmt
gmake
cd -

cmt co -r PhotonAnalysisTools-00-00-08 Reconstruction/egamma/egammaAnalysis/PhotonAnalysisTools
cd Reconstruction/egamma/egammaAnalysis/PhotonAnalysisTools/cmt
gmake
cd -

cmt co -r PhotonAnalysisAlgs-00-01-05 Reconstruction/egamma/egammaAnalysis/PhotonAnalysisAlgs
---> You need to edit the file PhotonCluster_jobOptions.py  :  Change the line
---> Version="v5_calh"
---> into
---> Version="v5_1_calh"
cd Reconstruction/egamma/egammaAnalysis/PhotonAnalysisAlgs/cmt
gmake
cd -

cmt co PhysicsAnalysis/HiggsPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils
cd PhysicsAnalysis/HiggsPhys/PhotonAnalysisUtils/cmt
gmake

---> To run PhotonAnalysisUtils, you need to use the jobO PAUanalysis_jobOptions.py (which also call CommonJobOptions.py)


---> Note : As there is a "bug" in PhotonAnalysisAlgs-00-01-05, the isem value is not correct and we still have to use the PAUphotonCorrectionTool from PhotonAnalysisUtils ---> Thi is why I have uncommented the line :
ToolSvc.PAUphotonSelector.PhotonIDbyCuts = 2
in CommonJobOptions.py

